"{\"uid\": \"rappler.com-sports-boxing-gold-medal-north-star-philippine-boxers-journey-paris-olympics-2024\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  SUMMARY  This is AI generated summarization, which may have errors.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 69, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 19, \"end\": 21, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"score\": 0.7957717088176868, \"rank\": 0.2566415797611556, \"text\": \"AI\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Artificial_intelligence\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For context, always refer to the full article.\", \"from\": 70, \"to\": 116, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Eumir Marcial Facebook page  Boxing has produced the most number of Olympians for the Philippines.\", \"from\": 118, \"to\": 216, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 204, \"end\": 215, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"score\": 0.9999833018771721, \"rank\": 1.669800401905652e-05, \"text\": \"Philippines\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Except for the 1924 and 1928 Games, the Philippines has sent a boxing representative in each of the last 20 editions it participated in, with Filipino boxers accounting for eight of the 14 medals the country has won in the history of the Olympics.\", \"from\": 218, \"to\": 465, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 258, \"end\": 269, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"score\": 0.9999833018771721, \"rank\": 1.669800401905652e-05, \"text\": \"Philippines\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\"}, {\"begin\": 360, \"end\": 368, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"score\": 0.9999999999995453, \"rank\": 6.702381338367384e-13, \"text\": \"Filipino\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So as it celebrates100 yearsof Olympic participation, highlighted by a breakthrough gold medal courtesy of weightlifterHidilyn Diazin the previous Tokyo Games, it should be fitting for the Philippines to capture that slippery boxing mint.\", \"from\": 467, \"to\": 705, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 656, \"end\": 667, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"score\": 0.9999833018771721, \"rank\": 1.669800401905652e-05, \"text\": \"Philippines\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That is the goal in the Paris Games as Nesthy Petecio, Carlo Paalam, and Eumir Marcial get another shot at Olympic glory, with debutants Hergie Bacyadan and Aira Villegas in tow.\", \"from\": 707, \"to\": 885, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 746, \"end\": 760, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nesthy_Petecio\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nesthy Petecio\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nesthy_Petecio\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nesthy_Petecio\"}, {\"begin\": 762, \"end\": 774, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlo_Paalam\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carlo Paalam\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlo_Paalam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlo_Paalam\"}, {\"begin\": 780, \"end\": 793, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eumir_Marcial\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Eumir Marcial\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eumir_Marcial\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Eumir_Marcial\"}, {\"begin\": 864, \"end\": 868, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aira\", \"score\": 0.999997842918272, \"rank\": 1.190116640242583e-06, \"text\": \"Aira\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aira\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aira\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It marks the Philippines' biggest boxing delegation since it also sent five boxers to the 1996 Atlanta Games, where Mansueto \\\"Onyok\\\" Velasco settled for silver following what many felt an incorrectly judged final loss to Bulgaria's Daniel Petrov.\", \"from\": 887, \"to\": 1133, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 900, \"end\": 911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"score\": 0.9999833018771721, \"rank\": 1.669800401905652e-05, \"text\": \"Philippines\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippines\"}, {\"begin\": 1003, \"end\": 1027, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Onyok_Velasco\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mansueto \\\"Onyok\\\" Velasco\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Onyok_Velasco\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Onyok_Velasco\"}, {\"begin\": 1108, \"end\": 1116, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bulgaria_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999905764319198, \"rank\": 9.423656617461281e-06, \"text\": \"Bulgaria\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bulgaria_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bulgaria_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1119, \"end\": 1132, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_Petrov\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3464961440937413e-21, \"text\": \"Daniel Petrov\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_Petrov\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daniel_Petrov\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's everyone's hope, for us to be able to finally get that elusive gold medal,\\\" said Association of Boxing Alliances in the Philippines (ABAP) secretary general Marcus Jarwin Manalo.\", \"from\": 1135, \"to\": 1321, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Of course, all of us want that.\", \"from\": 1323, \"to\": 1355, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's the North Star of the team.\\\"\", \"from\": 1356, \"to\": 1391, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But winning an Olympic gold is no easy feat.\", \"from\": 1393, \"to\": 1437, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And if there is one who knows that it takes great pains to achieve that, it is Petecio, who came oh-so close in Tokyo as she baggedsilverafter bowing to Japan's Irie Sena via unanimous decision in the final.\", \"from\": 1439, \"to\": 1646, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1551, \"end\": 1556, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.556362317859598e-19, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 1592, \"end\": 1597, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.5337402405829311, \"rank\": 0.836071752083296, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_women's_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1605, \"end\": 1609, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sena_dynasty\", \"score\": 0.9953746930529912, \"rank\": 0.004644701271416078, \"text\": \"Sena\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sena_dynasty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sena_dynasty\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While Sena will not be coming back to defend her throne following her retirement last year, the women's 57kg division still provides an arduous challenge, with Petecio regarding Tokyo bronze medalist Irma Testa of Italy, two-time world champion Lin Yu-ting of Chinese Taipei, and Asian titlist Karina Ibragimova of Kazakhstan as her strongest rivals.\", \"from\": 1648, \"to\": 1998, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1826, \"end\": 1831, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.556362317859598e-19, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 1848, \"end\": 1858, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irma_Testa\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Irma Testa\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irma_Testa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irma_Testa\"}, {\"begin\": 1862, \"end\": 1867, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9982341937154461, \"rank\": 0.0017552367127710875, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1893, \"end\": 1904, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lin Yu-ting\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\"}, {\"begin\": 1916, \"end\": 1922, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taipei\", \"score\": 0.6664086548468757, \"rank\": 0.5005807320512913, \"text\": \"Taipei\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taipei\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taipei\"}, {\"begin\": 1928, \"end\": 1933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Asian_Games\", \"score\": 1.0, \